The Constitution for a Just Cosmos and a Minimum-State Civilization
The Ultimate Motive: To foster a world so rooted in local accountability and creative wit that the need for hospitals, courts, police, and standing armies naturally evaporates.

I. The Pillar of Local Finality & Subsidiarity
Justice and resource management must begin and end at the source.

The Mandate: Disputes over land, water, or social friction must be settled by local leadership.

The Guardrail: Higher courts (National/Cosmic) supervise the process for fairness but are strictly forbidden from being used as "escape routes" for those wishing to drag a case to avoid a local verdict.

II. The Pillar of Proportional Equity (Discovery Law)
The treasures of the "Soil" or the "Stars" are shared through a transparent formula.

The Weightage: Distribution is calculated by (Investment + Research + Need) × Proximity. * The Goal: To replace the "Winner-Takes-All" land grab with a mathematical system of fair reward.

III. The Pillar of the 18th Elephant & The Generational Seal
No conflict shall outlive the generation that started it.

The Time-Bound Rule: All cases must be settled within 25 years (one generation).

The Settlement: If a deadlock persists, a creative "18th Elephant" (a non-destructive, witty third-way solution) is mandated. Breaking the "bat and ball" (resources) is a high crime.

IV. The Pillar of Active Community Supervision
The people living nearest to an infrastructure project (Road, Dam, Bridge) are its official inspectors.

Shared Stake: If the project is substandard, both the Contractor and the Neighbors share the fine. Silence in the face of poor work is considered complicity.

V. The Pillar of Honorable Ambassadorship
The era of the Ottran (Spy) and the "Shadow War" is ended.

Transparency: Success must be earned through merit and open research. Any advantage gained through sabotage, fraud, or character assassination results in the immediate forfeiture of resource rights.

VI. The Pillar of High-Status Accountability (The Manu-British Scale)
The Law uses the British Standard of Investigation (forensics and facts) and the Manu Standard of Punishment (moral weight).

The Ratio: The more "Learned" or powerful the offender, the heavier the punishment. Super-genius intellect used for loophole-seeking is treated as a crime against the Cosmos.

VII. The Pillar of Perpetual Evolution
This Charter is a living organism.

The Adaptation: Intellectuals of future generations may amend the methods of implementation to fight new forms of exploitation.

The Immutable Core: The "Basics"—Dharma, Truth, and Local Responsibility—can never be tampered with.

THE SEAL OF FINALITY
"Let us build each other’s houses so that no one desires to burn them down. Let us settle our debts while we breathe, so that even Yama’s Court remains empty. This is the end of the 'Broken Bat' and the beginning of the 'Universal Game'."
